what is pytest?


this is a small python tool , that runs small files ! that check wheather your code behaves correctly ! 


so you basically make a test function , where u call the origional function that needs to be tested ! 


def add_tax(price):
    return price * 1.1




def test_add_tax():
    assert add_tax(1000) == 1100



#so its esseantially rapping a your origional function with a test function ! 


a#after this you do 


python -m pytest 



If the assert is true, the test passes.
If the assert is false, the test fails.





so my confusion is ; why do we need to use pytest , if we can just make a branch , and test the code ! 

| Thing          | What it does                           | Problem                                    |
| -------------- | -------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| Branch         | Lets you safely experiment             | Does not prove your code works             |
| Manual testing | You click/run things yourself          | Easy to forget cases                       |
| Pytest         | Automatically checks expected behavior | Requires setup and discipline              |
| GitHub PR      | Lets you review changes                | Better when tests prove the branch is safe |







